casebody.data:
Damon, Respondent, v. New York, N. H. & H. R. Co., Appellant. (Common Pleas of New York City and County, General Term. November 17, 1890.) Appeal from seventh district court.

Argued before Daly, C. J., and Bischoff and Pryor, JJ.

Page & Taft, for appellant. Mr. Williams, for respondent.

No opinion. Appeal dismissed, and judgment affirmed, with costs.
